	h5.cd Selecting the Chemical Reaction
	p.cd Through my research, I found several viable options for activating agarose. I selected a reaction that was stable between 0-100°C and could be modified for various end applications (Spencer, Melo, Perez, & Weller, 2005). I then activated several millimeter width agarose beads and demonstrated positive and negative controls, both before and after melting. The results were very promising and supported my assumptions to move forward with the reaction.

